# Windsurf Rules ‚Äî fqc (High-Performance FASTQ Compressor)

## Project Identity

This is **fqc**, a Rust CLI tool and library for compressing genomic FASTQ files. It uses the ABC (Alignment-Based Compression) algorithm for short reads and Zstd for medium/long reads. MSRV is Rust 1.75.

## Build & Verify Commands

```bash
cargo build                    # dev build ‚Äî must compile cleanly
cargo test --lib --tests       # 97 tests, 0 failures expected
cargo clippy --all-targets     # 0 warnings (clippy pedantic enabled)
cargo fmt --all -- --check     # format check
```

Always run `cargo test --lib --tests` and `cargo clippy --all-targets` before committing.

## Project Layout

- `src/main.rs` ‚Äî CLI entry (clap derive): compress, decompress, info, verify commands
- `src/lib.rs` ‚Äî library re-exports
- `src/error.rs` ‚Äî `FqcError` (11 variants) + `ExitCode` mapping (0-5)
- `src/types.rs` ‚Äî `ReadRecord`, `QualityMode`, `IdMode`, `PeLayout`, `ReadLengthClass`
- `src/format.rs` ‚Äî FQC binary format structures (magic, headers, footer)
- `src/fqc_reader.rs` ‚Äî block-indexed archive reader with random access
- `src/fqc_writer.rs` ‚Äî archive writer with block index + finalize
- `src/reorder_map.rs` ‚Äî bidirectional read reorder map (ZigZag varint)
- `src/algo/` ‚Äî compression algorithms (ABC block_compressor, global_analyzer, quality_compressor, pe_optimizer)
- `src/commands/` ‚Äî CLI command implementations (compress, decompress, info, verify)
- `src/common/memory_budget.rs` ‚Äî system memory detection + ChunkingStrategy
- `src/fastq/parser.rs` ‚Äî FASTQ parser with validation, stats, PE, chunk reading
- `src/io/async_io.rs` ‚Äî AsyncReader/AsyncWriter/BufferPool
- `src/io/compressed_stream.rs` ‚Äî feature-gated gz/bz2/xz/zst transparent decompression
- `src/pipeline/` ‚Äî 3-stage Reader‚ÜíCompressor‚ÜíWriter pipelines (crossbeam channels)
- `tests/` ‚Äî 6 test suites: test_e2e (15), test_roundtrip (14), test_parser (19), test_reorder_map (23), test_format (15), test_types (11)

## Coding Rules

### Must Follow
- **MSRV 1.75** ‚Äî do not use APIs stabilized after Rust 1.75
- **No unsafe** ‚Äî `unsafe_code = "deny"` globally; only `#[allow(unsafe_code)]` on Windows FFI in `memory_budget.rs`
- **Clippy pedantic** ‚Äî 0 warnings; domain-specific allows configured in `Cargo.toml [lints.clippy]`
- **Use `log` crate** ‚Äî `log::info!`, `log::warn!`, `log::debug!`; never `println!` for status output
- **Use `thiserror`** ‚Äî new errors go in `FqcError` enum in `error.rs`, map in `exit_code()`
- **Feature-gated compression** ‚Äî gz/bz2/xz behind `#[cfg(feature)]` in `compressed_stream.rs`
- **Test before commit** ‚Äî all 97 tests must pass

### Style
- 4-space indent, max line width 120 (see `rustfmt.toml`)
- Imports grouped: std ‚Üí external ‚Üí crate (see `rustfmt.toml` `imports_granularity`)
- Section separators: `// ====...====` block comments for major sections
- No comments/docs changes unless explicitly asked

### Avoid
- Changing FQC binary format without bumping version
- Deleting or weakening existing tests
- Platform-specific paths ‚Äî use `std::path::Path`
- `unwrap()` in library code ‚Äî use `?` with `FqcError`
- Adding dependencies without justification

## Common Patterns

### Add a CLI flag
1. Add field to options struct in `src/commands/<cmd>.rs`
2. Add `#[arg]` to `Commands` enum in `src/main.rs`
3. Wire field in match arm in `main.rs`

### Add an error variant
1. Add variant to `FqcError` in `src/error.rs`
2. Add mapping in `FqcError::exit_code()`

### Add a compression format
1. Add `CompressionFormat` variant in `src/io/compressed_stream.rs`
2. Add magic bytes + extension detection
3. Add reader behind `#[cfg(feature)]`
4. Add optional dep + feature in `Cargo.toml`

### Add a test
- Use helpers: `compress_file()`, `decompress_file()`, `read_fastq_records()` from `test_e2e.rs`
- Create temp files, clean up after
- Round-trip: compress ‚Üí decompress ‚Üí compare record-by-record (id, sequence, quality)

